## Commit Convention

All commits follow [Conventional Commits v1.0.0](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/) from project setup forward. The `commit-msg` hook installed by `/dev-process-toolkit:setup` enforces this locally — non-conforming commits are rejected before they land.

**Subject** — `<type>(<scope>): <description>`, ≤ 72 characters.

- **Type** — one of `feat | fix | docs | style | refactor | perf | test | build | ci | chore | revert`.
- **Scope** — encouraged; the primary touched area (e.g., `feat(api): ...`, `fix(parser): ...`).
- **Breaking change** — append `!` (e.g., `feat!: drop legacy endpoint`). The `BREAKING CHANGE:` body footer is also accepted per spec.

**Tracker IDs** go in the footer:

```
Refs: <TICKET-ID>
```

(e.g., `Refs: <TICKET-ID>`, or in `mode: none` the short-ULID tail of the FR file). Multiple FRs in one commit get one `Refs:` line each.

**Sample messages:**

```
feat(parser): support nested array literals

Refs: PROJ-12
```

```
fix(api): handle null response from upstream timeout

Refs: PROJ-13
```

```
chore(release): v1.4.0

CHANGELOG bumped, README "Latest" line updated.

Release: v1.4.0 "Crisp"
Refs: M<N>
```

**Opt-in `commitlint`** — projects with Node/Bun tooling can swap the shell hook for a [commitlint](https://commitlint.js.org/)-delegating one via `/setup --commitlint`, which writes `commitlint.config.js` extending `@commitlint/config-conventional` and surfaces the install command (`bun add -D @commitlint/cli @commitlint/config-conventional`). The shell hook is the zero-dep default.

